main.name: Jorge Gonzalez
main.description: with a passion for User Experience and Design
main.bio: Energetic software engineer with the ability to pick up new languages and technologies as needed. Prior to being a software engineer, I worked as a dispatch for Global Trailer, a transportation company where I managed rates, deadlines, routes and delivery details according to the loads transported providing customers with the services that best suits their needs.

education.description: Software engineering training program covering full-stack development including, but not limited to JavaScript, Python, including an emphasis on cutting-edge frameworks like React/Redux and server-side technologies including Node.js, Express, and PostgreSQL.

work.title: Personal Shopper
work.description1: Responsible for liaising with customers to determine their specific needs, ultimate goals, budgets, and interests to find the appropriate items that best suit their needs.
work.description2: Interacting with customers to know/determine what they are looking for, provide advice and knowledge of the best products to purchase, process purchase, and help with exchanges or returns.
work.description3: Oversee the processing of customer orders, which involves processing orders on behalf of customers either via live chat, telephone calls, or email, and communicating with them to know what they are looking for, as well as any specific features they need the items to have.

work.company: Global Trailer | Houstan, TX / Oklahoma City, OK
work.title: Manager, Dispatch
work.description1: Operations Manager in a company that provides transportation services within and outside the state of Texas
work.description2: Responsabilities include: Provide great customer service, negotiate service rates, meet delivery dead lines and guarantee the safety of the drivers and the product transported
work.description3: Evaluate traffic routes and weather conditions

testimonials.text: Any fool can write code that a computer can understand. Good programmers write code that humans can understand.
A programming language is for thinking about programs, not for expressing programs you've already thought of. It should be a pencil, not a pen.
